===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
The bronze inscription was in the form of {{zh-l|*門|door}} + {{zh-l|*卝|locked door; two wooden sticks to lock a door}}. {{och-l|卝}} might also serve as a phonetic component. The whole character represents a door locked with two wooden sticks.

Then, the character slightly evolved into {{Han compound|門|𢇅|c1=s|c2=p|t1=door|ls=psc}}, in which two couples of rings similar to 幺幺 are visible on top of the two wooden sticks.

===Etymology 1===
Compare {{cog|tai-swe-pro|*klɔːnᴬ²||latch of door; rafter}}, whence {{cog|th|กลอน}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

